{"id":"326067410_The_Theory_of_Situational_Privacy_and_Self-Disclosure","abstract":"This chapter advances the theory of situational privacy and self-disclosure that aims at solving the identified gaps in the existing literature: First, it synthesizes independently developed theories of privacy and self-disclosure in one comprehensive theoretical rationale. Second, it provides an abstract framework that allows for classifying antecedents of self-disclosure into personal and environmental as well as non-situational and situational factors. Third, it restructures privacy-related concepts such as preventive privacy regulation behaviors, privacy perceptions, self-disclosure decision processes, and evaluation processes into a processual framework. This way, it allows for the investigation of such processes in both mediated and non-mediated communication situations. The chapter closes with a systematic guide for the application of the theory.","authors":["Philipp K. Masur"],"meta":["January 2019","DOI:10.1007/978-3-319-78884-5_7","In book: Situational Privacy and Self-Disclosure (pp.131-182)"],"references":["324270449_Privacy_in_Mediated_and_Nonmediated_Interpersonal_Communication_How_Subjective_Concepts_and_Situational_Perceptions_Influence_Behaviors","314157323_Entwicklung_und_Validierung_der_Online-Privatheitskompetenzskala_OPLIS","314076336_Privacy_attitudes_perceptions_and_behaviors_of_the_German_population","312507345_Online_Privacy_Concerns_and_Privacy_Management_A_Meta-Analytical_Review_Privacy_Concerns_Meta-Analysis","303749254_Cultural_Differences_in_Social_Media_Use_Privacy_and_Self-Disclosure","301519707_Do-It-Yourself_Data_Protection_-_Empowerment_or_Burden","295859158_Disclosure_Management_on_Social_Network_Sites_Individual_Privacy_Perceptions_and_User-Directed_Privacy_Strategies","278414419_Privacy_Recalibration_in_Personal_Relationships_Rule_Usage_Before_and_After_an_Incident_of_Privacy_Turbulence","272852450_Performing_for_one's_imagined_audience_Social_st